title: "401(k) & IRA Rollovers | Capital Wealth"
description: "Expert 401(k) and IRA rollover guidance in Lehi, Utah. Maximize your retirement savings with strategic rollover planning from a fiduciary financial advisor."
breadcrumbs:
  - { name: "Home", url: "/" }
  - { name: "Services", url: "/services/" }
  - { name: "401(k) & IRA Rollovers", url: "/services/401k-ira-rollover/" }
faqSchema:
  - question: "Will I pay taxes on a rollover?"
    answer: "A direct rollover from a traditional 401(k) to a traditional IRA is tax-free. A Roth conversion creates a taxable event in the year you convert. We model both scenarios to show you the long-term impact and help you decide if a Roth conversion makes sense."
  - question: "Should I roll over my 401(k) or leave it?"
    answer: "It depends. Some 401(k) plans have low fees and great investment options — in which case leaving it might make sense. We compare your plan's fees and fund options against what's available in an IRA and recommend the best path forward."
  - question: "How long does a rollover take?"
    answer: "Most direct rollovers take 2-4 weeks from start to finish. We handle all the paperwork and coordination with your old plan administrator to ensure a smooth, tax-free transfer."
  - question: "What is a direct rollover vs indirect rollover?"
    answer: "A direct rollover transfers funds directly between custodians with no taxes withheld. An indirect rollover sends you a check, and you have 60 days to deposit it into an IRA or face taxes and penalties. We only do direct rollovers to avoid complications."
  - question: "Can I roll my 401(k) into a Roth IRA?"
    answer: "Yes, but it creates a taxable event. We analyze whether the long-term tax-free growth in a Roth IRA outweighs the upfront tax cost based on your income, timeline, and retirement goals."
