<section class="ep-faq">
  <div class="ep-faq-inner">
    <div>
      <span class="ep-chapter-label">Common Questions</span>
      <h2 class="ep-faq-title">Rollover FAQ</h2>
      <p class="ep-faq-sub">Get answers to common 401(k) and IRA rollover questions.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="ep-btn-ghost">Ask About Rollovers</a>
    </div>
    <div>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Will I pay taxes on a rollover? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>A direct rollover from a traditional 401(k) to a traditional IRA is tax-free. A Roth conversion creates a taxable event in the year you convert. We model both scenarios to show you the long-term impact and help you decide if a Roth conversion makes sense.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Should I roll over my 401(k) or leave it? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>It depends. Some 401(k) plans have low fees and great investment options — in which case leaving it might make sense. We compare your plan's fees and fund options against what's available in an IRA and recommend the best path forward.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How long does a rollover take? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Most direct rollovers take 2-4 weeks from start to finish. We handle all the paperwork and coordination with your old plan administrator to ensure a smooth, tax-free transfer.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What is a direct rollover vs indirect rollover? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>A direct rollover transfers funds directly between custodians with no taxes withheld. An indirect rollover sends you a check, and you have 60 days to deposit it into an IRA or face taxes and penalties. We only do direct rollovers to avoid complications.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Can I roll my 401(k) into a Roth IRA? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Yes, but it creates a taxable event. We analyze whether the long-term tax-free growth in a Roth IRA outweighs the upfront tax cost based on your income, timeline, and retirement goals.</p></div>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

